o toilet facilities and nice bracing showers during summer. I have found free hot showers by word of mouth and if things get tight money wise I know where to get a free meal or a bakery that sells its old stock for $1.50 a bag. &lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;I hear people say that they usually get saved in the nick of time. Job turns up when desperately needed, a couch becomes available or you close a much needed deal. But guess what...it doesn&amp;#39;t always come up roses. For me one after another I lost jobs, ventures just don&amp;#39;t come off. One after another after another.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;I think what I am trying to say is homelessness is generally forced on people. Not planned. I am far better off than most homeless. I have a vehicle to live in and a nice environment  to while away the time. But most importantly I have hope.  </content><link rel='edit' type='application/atom+xml' href='http://www.blogger.com/feeds/8752543/109831369489082264/comments/default/316266074445040449'/><link rel='self' type='application/atom+xml' href='http://www.blogger.com/feeds/8752543/109831369489082264/comments/default/316266074445040449'/><link rel='alternate' type='text/html' href='http://guide2homelessness.blogspot.com/2004/10/im-not-bum.html?showComment=1437795501443#c316266074445040449' title=''/><author><name>Steve</name><email>noreply@blogger.com</email><gd:image rel='http://schemas.google.com/g/2005#thumbnail' width='16' height='16' src='http://img1.blogblog.com/img/blank.gif'/></author><thr:in-reply-to xmlns:thr='http://purl.org/syndication/thread/1.0' href='http://guide2homelessness.blogspot.com/2004/10/im-not-bum.html' ref='tag:blogger.com,1999:blog-8752543.post-109831369489082264' source='http://www.blogger.com/feeds/8752543/posts/default/109831369489082264' type='text/html'/><gd:extendedProperty name="blogger.itemClass" value="pid-555406524"/><gd:extendedProperty name="blogger.displayTime" value="8:38 PM"/></entry><entry><id>tag:blogger.com,1999:blog-8752543.pos