itle type='text'> 7/8/2014&#xa;Homeless in Palm Desert&#xa;I am a 44 year o...</title><content type='html'> 7/8/2014&lt;br /&gt;Homeless in Palm Desert&lt;br /&gt;I am a 44 year old female who is terrified I may become homeless within the next month.  I recently have been diagnosed with peripheral neuropathy and I am in severe pain chronic pain.  They are running tests to determine cause of it, like ms or another autoimmune disorder. My problem is I currently live with my fiance who no longer wants me as a dependant.  I have not worked at his request for 3 1/2 years to take care of him and his children.  I am not living up to my end of the bargain and can no longer cook, clean, shop due to my extreme pain.  I am in bed with ice on my feet constantly and most of the time can not walk on my feet.  I have been working since I was 15 (except the last 3) and was a clinical research coordinator making good money.  Now I make nothing.  I do get food stamps monthly.  My problem is I live in the desert in California and I do not have a car.  Everything we have he believes is his and is in his name anyway.  I am petrified by fear of being on the streets with no car, at least then I would feel safe.  I am terrified of being raped or worse.  I am cognitively impaired as well due to this disorder that they are trying to diagnose, but can not mentally work especially when you factor in the strong medications I am taking.  Half the time I am a zombie.  This is not a good state to be in if you are a homeless female.  I do not have any family and do not have any friends as my two dearest friends have passed recently.  Any advice to point me in the right direction would be greatly appreciated.  Also my Dr. appointments are 15 miles away from the nearest shelter.  Please please if you have any information!!!</content><link rel='edit' type='application/atom+xml' href='http://www.blogger.com/feeds/8752543/109831369489082264/comments/default/158586718928348022'/><link rel='self' type='ap